Additional Backend Features
1. Notification & Alert Engine
Objective

Automatically notify users when important operational events occur, eliminating the need for manual monitoring.

Trigger Events
Driver
License expires within:
30 days
15 days
7 days
Today
Vehicle
Insurance expiry
Fitness certificate expiry
Maintenance due
Trips
Trip delayed
Trip cancelled
Expenses
Expense exceeds predefined threshold
User Stories
Fleet Manager
Receive maintenance reminders
Receive vehicle document expiry alerts
Safety Officer
Receive driver license expiry alerts
Dispatcher
Receive delayed trip notifications
Functional Requirements
Notification Generation

System automatically creates notifications when trigger conditions are met.

Fields

Notification ID
User ID
Title
Description
Notification Type
Priority
Status
Created At
Read At

Status

Unread
Read
Archived

Priority

Low
Medium
High
Critical
Backend APIs
GET /notifications

Returns notifications for logged-in user
PATCH /notifications/{id}/read
PATCH /notifications/read-all
DELETE /notifications/{id}
Business Rules
Notifications are role-specific.
Duplicate notifications should not be generated.
Expired notifications should archive automatically after 30 days.
